  "prompt": "Can an L2 visa holder work without EAD?",
  "response": "No, an L2 visa holder cannot work in the United States without obtaining an Employment Authorization Document (EAD). Here are the key points:\n\n1. Basic Rule:\n- L2 visa holders are dependents of L1 visa holders\n- They must apply for and receive an EAD before legally working\n\n2. EAD Application Process:\n- File Form I-765 (Application for Employment Authorization)\n- Must be approved before starting any employment\n- Can apply after entering the U.S. with L2 status\n\n3. Eligibility:\n- Spouse of L1 visa holder is eligible to apply for EAD\n- Unmarried children under 21 are not eligible to work\n\n4. Processing:\n- EAD processing typically takes 3-5 months\n- Can work only after receiving the actual EAD card\n\n5. Restrictions:\n- Working without an EAD is considered unauthorized employment\n- Can result in serious immigration consequences, including potential deportation\n\nAlways consult with an immigration attorney or USCIS for the most current and specific guidance regarding your individual situation.",
